Object oriented programming

////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

Encapsulation -> Act to combine Properties(Variables) and Methods related to same entity.

example : 

struct book {

  int bookid;
  char title[20];
  float price;
  
  void input() {
    cin >> bookid >> title >> price;
  }
  
  void display() {
    cout << bookid >> title >> price;
  }
};

In above structure, we have 5 member : 3 Variables, 2 Methods.

////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

Important Points to remember

Public, Private Members

Public : You can access any member outside the structure
Private : You can access only in structure definition

Importance : You can protect your data from begin corrupted. See this video [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JTNlO8qwESw&list=PLLYz8uHU480j37APNXBdPz7YzAi4XlQUF&index=18].

Struct vs Class

In struct, by default all members are public 
In class, by default all members are private
and all the remaining comcept are exactly same.

